    <example xml:id="auto_zz84kntj">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_5nkg88hz">
                Find the value of <m>t</m> and <m>w</m> in the figure shown below (Using sine and cosine tables).
            </p>
            <image width="50%">
            <latex-image label="Triangle14">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                    
                    % Draw the triangle
                    \draw [very thick] (0,0) node[left] {$C$} -- (6,0) node[right] {$B$} -- (6,5) node[above] {$A$} -- cycle;
                    
                    % Hypotenuse Label
                    \draw [very thick](3,2.5) node[left] {8 cm};

                    % Right angle symbol at B
                    \draw[very thick] (6,0) -- ++(-0.4,0) -- ++(0,0.4) -- ++(0.4,0);
                    
                    % Sides Labels
                    \node[right] at (6,2.5) {$t$ cm};
                    \node[below] at (3,0) {$w$ cm};

                    % Angle at C
                    \draw [very thick](0.8,0) arc[start angle=0,end angle=57.6,radius=0.5];
                    \node[right] at (1,0.4) { $54.7^\circ$};
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
                
            </image>

        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_hudlosgx">
                Recall that; 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_3te13278">
                <m>\sin\,\theta=\frac{\text{opposite}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}=\frac{t}{8}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_uvoyv4s5">
                <m>\cos\,\theta=\frac{\text{adjacent}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}=\frac{w}{8}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_o61to0p7">
                Therefore, <md>
                    <mrow> \sin\,54.7^\circ=\amp \frac{t}{8}</mrow>
                    <mrow> 8\,\sin\,54.7^\circ=\amp t</mrow>
                    
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_ha98t1wz">
                But, from tables of sine, <m>\sin\,54.7^\circ \approx \sin \,55^\circ = 0.8192</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_fltb7iup">
                Therefore, <md>
                    <mrow> t =\amp 8 \times 0.8192 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp 6.5536 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>

            <p xml:id="auto_as9pa3te">
                <md>
                    <mrow> \cos\,54.7^\circ=\amp \frac{w}{8}</mrow>
                    <mrow> 8\,\cos\,54.7^\circ=\amp w</mrow>
                    
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_cljciluv">
                But, from tables of cosine, <m>\cos\,54.7^\circ \approx \cos\,55^\circ = 0.5736</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_0dj4n6fq">
                Therefore, <md>
                    <mrow> w =\amp 8 \times 0.5736 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp 4.5888 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
        <example xml:id="auto_ojfest2s">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_06oir480">
                    Using tangents in your mathematical tables, find <m>\alpha</m> as shown in the figure below.
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="Triangle10">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1.2]
                       % Draw the triangle PQR
                        \coordinate (P) at (4,3); % Adjust coordinates as needed
